title: Grateful Dead Live at Music Hall on 1971-04-08
description:
Set 1

Truckin', Bertha, Next Time You See Me, Playin' In The Band, Loser, Beat It On Down The Line, Second That Emotion, Sugar Magnolia, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Casey Jones

Set 2

Dark Star-> Saint Stephen-> Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, Sing Me Back Home, Cumberland Blues, Greatest Story Ever Told-> Johnny B. Goode, Good Lovin'-> Drums-> Good Lovin'

Other artist(s): NRPS

reviews.review_text: - Thought I'd listen to a newer version of this & see what I thought. Good show! Not the greatest. First Dark Star in a while, and so forth.

Excellent Show! I don't know what the reviewer above is talking about, "Good show, not the greatest", !!!! What? This is an incredible ;show and the Dark Star is just beautiful, I'm not the only one who thinks so cuz Deadbase puts it as the #14 show of 1971!

Hometown Show hitched down to NYC with another Cat for the Manhattan Center Run.  4th 5th 6th, I left Marlborough ,Mass to go to those shows, Boston is about 40 minutes east  of where I left from. We missed the Boston show. find this a bit funny decades later. Why we didnt just pick up tour in Boston is beyond me. Trips are for kids.. typical fix it, tune it show in Boston. enjoyable nun the less. TY for putting up.

Good Show... Not the greatest? Checking out other reviews occasionally entertains me while I'm listening! Usually while taking a break from letting my mind wander...wanderin' Anyway, I appreciate this gentleman's passion about ...how f**king awesome this show is... OMG! 
I think if one stays for the next...and more... bunch of shows, as they arrive at Fillmore East NYC it seems that its not the greatest... to each his own, but could it also be that having been weened on the early 80s, EVERYTHING IS AWESOME! Seems to me what I've encountered... then again, I have an appreciation for the 80s too!
Any and all shows available That we have them at all. That wonderful people have worked hard to make them better. Thank you for it. Sing Me Back Home. Thank you.
